= max(max_values)\n        return total\n```\n\nThis solution follows the problem's requirements by iteratively removing the greatest value from each row, adding the maximum of these values to the total, and repeating the process until the grid is empty. The constraints are handled efficiently given the maximum size of the grid is 50x50.", "estimated_date": 1670716800000}